-- Regal Said to Halt ‘Iron Man 3’ Sales in Dispute With Disney
-- B y   M i c h a e l   W h i t e
-- 2013-04-17T21:24:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-17/regal-said-to-halt-iron-man-3-sales-in-dispute-with-disney.html
Regal Entertainment Group (RGC) , the
largest U.S. theater chain, stopped selling advance tickets to
 Walt Disney Co. (DIS) ’s “Iron Man 3” in a fee dispute with the
studio, a person with knowledge of the situation said.  Regal joins the second-largest cinema operator, AMC
Entertainment, in halting sales for the film from Disney’s
Marvel unit.  Regal’s action was reported earlier by Deadline.com. and
the Los Angeles Times.  To contact the reporter on this story:
